==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Splash
<hw>Splash</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Splashed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Splashing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to
<ets>plash</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To strike and dash about, as
water, mud, etc.; to plash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To spatter water, mud, etc., upon; to wet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Splash
<hw>Splash</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To strike and dash about water,
mud, etc.; to dash in such a way as to spatter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Splash
<hw>Splash</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Water, or water and
dirt, thrown upon anything, or thrown from a puddle or the like; also, a
spot or daub, as of matter which wets or disfigures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A noise made by striking upon or in a
liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splashboard</ent>⟦br⟧
